 81st season overall, seventh as a member of the [[Mountain West Conference]] and fifth within the Mountain Division. The Broncos played their home games at [[Albertsons Stadium]] in [[Boise, Idaho|Boise]], [[Idaho]]. They were led by fourth-year head coach [[Bryan Harsin]]. They finished the season 11\u20133, 7\u20131 in Mountain West play to win the Mountain Division. They defeated West Division champion [[2017 Fresno State Bulldogs football team|Fresno State]] in the [[2017 Mountain West Conference Football Championship Game|Mountain West Championship Game]] to become Mountain West champions. They were invited to the [[2017 Las Vegas Bowl|Las Vegas Bowl]] where they defeated [[2017 Oregon Ducks football team|Oregon]].\n\n==Preseason==\n===Award watch lists===\nListed in the order that they were released.\n\n'''[[Rimington Trophy]]''' \u2013 Sr. C Mason Hampton<ref>{{cite web|title=Rimington Trophy Press Release|url=http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/bosu/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/2016-17/misc_non_event/2017RimingtonSpringList.pdf|date=May 22, 2017|accessdate=June 6, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Chuck Bednarik Award]]''' \u2013 Jr. DT David Moa<ref>{{cite web|title=2017 Bednarik Award Watch List|url=http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/bosu/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/2017-18/misc_non_event/2017_Bednarik_Award_Watch_List.pdf|date=July 10, 2017|accessdate=July 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Maxwell Award]]''' \u2013 Jr. QB [[Brett Rypien]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2017 Maxwell Award Watch List|url=http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/bosu/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/2017-18/misc_non_event/2017_Maxwell_Award_Watch_List.pdf|date=July 10, 2017|accessdate=July 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Bronko Nagurski Trophy]]''' \u2013 Jr. DT David Moa<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Bronko Nagurski Trophy watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-13/college-football-2017-bronko-nagurski-trophy-watch-list|date=July 14, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Outland Trophy]]''' \u2013 Sr. OT Archie Lewis & Jr. DT David Moa<ref>{{cite web|title=2017 OUTLAND TROPHY WATCH LIST UNVEILED|url=http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/bosu/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/2017-18/misc_non_event/2017_outland_trophy_preseason.pdf|date=July 13, 2017|accessdate=July 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[John Mackey Award]]''' \u2013 Sr. TE Jake Roh<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 John Mackey Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-11/college-football-2017-john-mackey-award-watch-list|date=July 14, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Paul Hornung Award]]''' \u2013 Sr. WR Cedrick Wilson<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Paul Hornung Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-17/college-football-2017-paul-hornung-award-watch-list|date=July 17, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Fred Biletnikoff Award]]''' \u2013 Sr. WR Cedrick Wilson<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Biletnikoff Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-18/college-football-2017-biletnikoff-award-watch-list|date=July 18, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Wuerffel Trophy]]''' \u2013 Jr. QB Brett Rypien<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Danny Wuerffel Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-18/college-football-2017-danny-wuerffel-award-watch-list|date=July 18, 2017|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Davey O'Brien Award]]''' \u2013 Jr. QB Brett Rypien<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Davey O'Brien Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-19/college-football-2017-davey-obrien-award-watch-list|date=July 19, 2017|accessdate=July 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Walter Camp Award]]''' \u2013 Jr. QB Brett Rypien<ref>{{cite web|title=College football: 2017 Walter Camp Award watch list|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2017-07-21/college-football-2017-walter-camp-award-watch-list|date=July 21, 2017|accessdate=July 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Manning Award]]''' \u2013 Jr. QB Brett Rypien<ref>{{cite web|title=Manning Award Watch List, 2017-18|url=https://www.allstatesugarbowl.org/site980.php|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Mountain West media days===\nAt the Mountain West media days, held at the [[Cosmopolitan of Las Vegas|Cosmopolitan]] in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], the Broncos were picked as the overwhelming favorites to win the Mountain Division title, receiving 21 of a possible 28 first place votes.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tust|first1=Jay|title=Boise State and San Diego State picked to meet in 2017 MW Championship Game|url=http://www.ktvb.com/sports/ncaaf/boise-state/boise-state-and-san-diego-state-picked-to-meet-in-2017-mw-championship-game/459373224|website=KTVB.com|publisher=TEGNA|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref> Sr. OL Mason Hampton was selected to the all-conference first team offense. Jr. DL David Moa and Jr. DB Tyler Horton were selected to the all-conference first team defense.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gagliardi|first1=Robert|title=UW's Allen, Wingard named preseason MW players of the year|url=http://www.wyosports.net/university_of_wyoming/football/uw-s-allen-wingard-named-preseason-mw-players-of-the/article_70219352-7142-11e7-ba68-2fb8eec27695.html|website=WyoSports.net|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Media poll===\n====Mountain Division====\n# Boise State \u2013 161 (21)\n# Colorado State \u2013 135 (6)\n# Wyoming \u2013 114 (1)\n# Air Force \u2013 82\n# New Mexico \u2013 68\n# Utah State \u2013 28\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\n| poll = [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Mountain\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 2\n| time = 1:45 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[2017 Troy Trojans football team|Troy]]\n| site_stadium = [[Albertsons Stadiu